{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"magarcia","author":"Martin Garcia"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"8186c576-12d1-5dd4-8d53-97385061ec37","html":"<p>Last Tuesday I enjoyed a talk of <a href=\"http://misko.hevery.com/about/\">Miško Hevery</a>\nabout Angular2 thanks to guys of <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/AngularJS-Beers/\">AngularBeers</a>.\nIt was a talk about what is coming with Angular 2 and the key point with which\nwe have to stay is that Angluar leave the concept of frontend framework to\nbecome a full a platform.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/cc4c90d4e876355248d820f1cab4b58f/8e062/angularbeers-with-misko-hevery.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 735px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 63.6734693877551%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/cc4c90d4e876355248d820f1cab4b58f/1d566/angularbeers-with-misko-hevery.webp 200w,\n/static/cc4c90d4e876355248d820f1cab4b58f/62e5d/angularbeers-with-misko-hevery.webp 400w,\n/static/cc4c90d4e876355248d820f1cab4b58f/cb923/angularbeers-with-misko-hevery.webp 735w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/cc4c90d4e876355248d820f1cab4b58f/904c5/angularbeers-with-misko-hevery.jpg 200w,\n/static/cc4c90d4e876355248d820f1cab4b58f/65c48/angularbeers-with-misko-hevery.jpg 400w,\n/static/cc4c90d4e876355248d820f1cab4b58f/8e062/angularbeers-with-misko-hevery.jpg 735w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n          src=\"/static/cc4c90d4e876355248d820f1cab4b58f/8e062/angularbeers-with-misko-hevery.jpg\"\n          alt=\"miskohevery\"\n          title=\"\"\n          src=\"/static/cc4c90d4e876355248d820f1cab4b58f/8e062/angularbeers-with-misko-hevery.jpg\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n      </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n<em>Sara (a good coworker and better friend), Miško and me</em></p>\n<p>But, apart from this, I would like to remark a couple of things that will make\nAngular 2 a powerful option in a near future.</p>\n<h2 id=\"offline-compile\"><a href=\"#offline-compile\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Offline compile</h2>\n<p>What does this means? Templates have been one of the places where mistakes are made\nsince Angular 1. Even if we introduce TypeScript or lint tools, we couldn’t be\nable to detect mistakes in templates until they are evaluated at the runtime.\nUntil now Angular 1.X compiles the templates each time they should be rendered.</p>\n<p>With Angular 2 (without offline compile) the templates are compiled only once.\nBut with offline compiling the templates are compiled on build time to\nJavaScript so it will be never compiled in the browser. The benefits we obtain\nhere is that it enables us to statically type-check our templates with\nTypeScript, which is awesome, in addition to skipping the runtime compilation\nand smaller library size.</p>\n<h2 id=\"angular-universal\"><a href=\"#angular-universal\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Angular Universal</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Universal (isomorphic) JavaScript support for Angular 2.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>With Angular Universal, we can run Angular 2 in the server side and this gives\nus some advantages:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Better Perceived Performance:</strong> The users will instantly see a server-rendered\nview which greatly improves perceived performance and the overall user\nexperience.</li>\n<li><strong>Optimized for Search Engines:</strong> Server-side pre-rendering is a reliable way to\nensure that all search engines can access your content.</li>\n<li><strong>Site Preview:</strong> Ensure that Facebook, Twitter, and all other social media apps\ncorrectly display a preview image of your app. (I deal with this problem before\nand is a pain in the ass)</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"extra-the-slides\"><a href=\"#extra-the-slides\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Extra: the slides</h2>\n<div>\n          <div\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\"\n            style=\"padding-bottom: 56.285714285714285%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden;margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\"\n          >\n            <iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1pIS0dhazArjoDHO1FLK1sEC8iO6rnGLw-WXFIiqafzc/embed?start=false&amp;loop=false&amp;delayms=3000\" title=\"Angular 2\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen style=\"\n            position: absolute;\n            top: 0;\n            left: 0;\n            width: 100%;\n            height: 100%;\n          \"></iframe>\n          </div>\n          </div>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"title":"AngularBeers with Miško Hevery","date":"June 26, 2016","dateRaw":"2016-06-26","spoiler":null},"fields":{"slug":"/angularbeers-with-misko-hevery/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/angularbeers-with-misko-hevery/","date":"2016-06-26","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/moving-big-parts-to-angular-2/","directoryName":"moving-big-parts-to-angular-2"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Moving big parts to Angular 2","date":"2016-06-12"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/midterm/","directoryName":"midterm"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Midterm","date":"2016-06-29"}}}}